  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div xml:id="AN13-kilavi"></div>
        <div xml:id="AN13">
            <lg type="edition"><l><choice><seg>taṇkaṭaṟ</seg><seg>taṉkaṭaṟ</seg></choice> piṟanta mutti ṉāramu</l>
<l>muṉaitiṟai koṭukkun tuppiṟ ṟaṉmalait</l>
<l>teṟalaru marapiṟ kaṭavuṭ pēṇik</l>
<l>kuṟavar tanta canti ṉāramu</l>
<l>mirupē rāramu meḻilpeṟa vaṇiyun</l>
<l>tiruvīḻ mārpiṟ ṟeṉṉavaṉ maṟavaṉ</l>
<l>kuḻiyiṟ koṇṭa marāa yāṉai</l>
<l>moḻiyi ṉuṇarttuñ ciṟuvarai yallatu</l>
<l>varainilai <choice><seg>yiṉṟi</seg><seg>yaṉṟi</seg></choice> yiravalark kīyum</l>
<l><choice><seg>vaḷvā</seg><seg>vaḷaivā</seg></choice> yampiṉ kōṭaip porunaṉ</l>
<l>paṇṇi taiiya <choice><seg>payaṉkeḻu</seg><seg>payaṅkeḻu</seg></choice> vēḷviyiṉ</l>
<l>viḻumitu nikaḻva tāyiṉun teṟkērpu</l>
<l>kaḻimaḻai <choice><seg>yoḻinta</seg><seg>poḻinta</seg></choice> poḻutuko ḷamaiyattuc</l>
<l>cāya liṉṟuṇai yivaṭpirin tuṟaiyi</l>
<l>ṉōyiṉ ṟāka ceyporuḷ vayiṟpaṭa</l>
<l>māci <choice><seg>ṟūmaṭi</seg><seg>ṟūumaṭi</seg></choice> virinta cēkkaik</l>
<l>kavaviṉ puṟāmaik kaḻika <choice><seg>vaḷavā</seg><seg>vaḷavaya</seg></choice></l>
<l><choice><seg>yaḻaṉuti</seg><seg>luḻaṉuti</seg></choice> yaṉṉa tō<supplied>kai</supplied> yīṉṟa</l>
<l>kaḻaṉi nelliṉ kavaimuta lalaṅka</l>
<l>ṉirampakaṉ ceṟuviṉ varampaṇai yākat</l>
<l><choice><seg>tuyilvarap</seg><seg>tuyalvarap</seg></choice> pulampoṭu vanta poḻutukoḷ</l>
<l>vāṭai yilaṅkupūṅ karumpi ṉērkaḻai</l>
<l>yirunta veṇkuruku narala vīcu</l>
<l>nuṇpaḵ ṟuvalaiya taṇpaṉi nāḷē.</l></lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Even if something excellent were to happen,</l>
<l rend="indent">	like the fruitful sacrifice performed by Paṇṇi,</l>
<l rend="indent">	the warrior of Kōṭai with <choice><seg>sharp-mouthed </seg><seg>bend-mouthed </seg></choice> arrows,</l>
<l rend="indent">	who gives to beggars not only the stability of a mountain,</l>
<l rend="indent">	[but] moreover small mountains directed by words,</l>
<l rend="indent">	[that is,] untamed elephants taken in pits,</l>
<l><choice><seg>	[or performed </seg><seg>	[or </seg></choice> by]<note place="foot">There is no syntactic link to connect the first six lines to the rest, unless we take it simply as an apposition to Paṇṇi, that is, as an alternative lord of the sacrifice.</note> the bold man of the Southern [king, his] chest desired by Śrī,</l>
<l rend="indent">	who adorns himself gracefully with two great garlands,</l>
<l rend="indent">	the string of pearls born in <choice><seg>the cool </seg><seg>his </seg></choice> sea</l>
<l rend="indent">	and the sandal from the trees given by the hill people,</l>
<l rend="indent">	paying respect to the god according to the custom difficult to violate(?)</l>
<l rend="indent">	of his mountain, with a zeal that gives tribute from the front,</l>
<l>if you stay separated from her, [your] graceful pleasing <choice><seg>mate,</seg><seg>mate</seg></choice> </l>
<l>on the occasion to be used<note place="foot">Here it is also possible to read kōḷ amaiyattu and refer to the present stellar constallation, as an auspicious time. Of course that would make the foot hypermetrical.</note>, the time when the passing <choice><seg>clouds stay behind,</seg><seg>rain flows,</seg></choice> </l>
<l rend="indent">	rising to the South,</l>
<l>let them pass in not having the pleasure of embracing,</l>
<l rend="indent">	on the bed spread with spotless pure cloth,</l>
<l>to be suffered on account of the wealth to be made, so as to be pain today,</l>
<l>– the days of cool dew in many fine drops,</l>
<l rend="indent">	when the north wind,</l>
<l rend="indent">	taking the time that comes with <choice><seg>loneliness when sleep [should] come,</seg><seg>loneliness, so that it comes in to swinging motion,</seg></choice> </l>
<l rend="indent">	with the endlessly wide field ridges for a bed,</l>
<l><choice><seg>	to the </seg><seg>	the </seg></choice> swaying in the forked [halms] of paddy in the fields</l>
<l><choice><seg>	brought forth from the </seg><seg>	brought forth from </seg></choice> sheaths, like <choice><seg>tips of fire in </seg><seg>tips, ploughing </seg></choice> the fertile <choice><seg>opening,</seg><seg>paddy field,</seg></choice> </l>
<l rend="indent">	hurls so that the white egret calls out,</l>
<l rend="indent">	perched on the pretty shafts of sugarcane with shining flowers.</l></lg>
        </div>
